PEOPLE 
Metrobank, an independent bank based in Los Angeles, has promoted five 
executives. Robert P. Bulseco was named president and chief administrative 
officer. He was an executive vice president. Other executives promoted: Robert 
Robie, vice chairman and chief credit officer; David Malone, executive vice 
president and chief financial officer; Paul Alexander, executive vice president 
of the loan division; Sharon Canup, corporate senior vice president, and 
Michael Provencio, corporate senior vice president. 
